'''Ved Kennede''' served as a [[Emperor's Royal Guard/Legends|Royal Guard]] to [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]]. Palpatine considered him one of his most loyal followers and, as a result, entrusted him with the position of [[Master Instructor]] at the [[Emperor's Royal Guard/Legends|Imperial Royal Guard]] facility on [[Yinchorr/Legends|Yinchorr]]. Ved Kennede was one of [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine's]] most trusted guards and advisors. He was also a Councilor in the Council but did not preform a normal Councilor's duties.

Ved Kennede trained [[Kir Kanos]] and [[Carnor Jax]] amongst other candidates, and was one of the last Guardsmen [[Attack on the Imperial Royal Guard Academy|killed]] by Jax's [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]] on [[Yinchorr/Legends|Yinchorr]] following the death of [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine's]] last clone. However, his son [[Tav Kennede|Tav]] remained loyal to Kanos, after the former Royal Guard brought news of his father's death. Kennede's son was, by that time, aiding the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]], having seen that the Empire his father loved no longer existed.

